<h2>
2.조명
</h2>
</p>
<p>
  <a>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incandescent_light_bulb</a><br>
  <a>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LED_lamp</a><br>
  <a>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gas-discharge_lamp</a><br>
  <a>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arc_lamp</a><br>
</p>
<p>
크게 4가지로 위키에선 구분하고있다.<br>
하위 분류도 상당히 많음.
</p>
<p>
그중 arc lamp는 상당히 생소하다<br>
  <img src= http://electricmuseum.com/wp-content/uploads/jen2.jpg><br>
 
"Arc lamp" or "arc light" is the general term for a class of lamps that produce light by an electric arc (also called a voltaic arc). <br>
The lamp consists of two electrodes, first made from carbon but typically made today of tungsten, which are separated by a gas. <br>
The type of lamp is often named by the gas contained in the bulb; including neon, argon,xenon, krypton, sodium, metal halide, and mercury, or by the type of electrode as in carbon-arc lamps. <br>
The commonfluorescent lamp is a low-pressure mercury arc lamp.
</p>
<p>
  <a>http://terms.naver.com/entry.nhn?docId=1121818&cid=200000000&categoryId=200003055</a><br>
전극 사이에 전류가 흐를 때 생기는 아크의 발광을 이용한 등.<br>
이라는 아주 간단한 요약. 알기 쉬운 한글.
</p>
